result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Michelle L Dupor was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Michelle L Dupor was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Defendant Michelle L Dupor in court with attorney Carl William Chesshir.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 and 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.

  The defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT 1:

HUBER:  110 days, w/Standard Release Conditions . Defendant to report to Huber facility by 5:00 p.m. on 7/20/16. May be served in Milwaukee County but the Court does NOT authorize electronic monitoring.

FINE: $1229.00 (apply cash bail and to be paid as a condition of probation on count #2);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid as a condition of probation on Count #2).

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to New Berlin Police Department. (to be paid as a condition of probation).

TRANSCRIPT FEE:  $8.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to District Attorney. (to be paid as a condition of probation).

D/L REVOCATION: 18 months;

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 18 months;

Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel on:  11/9/16. Defendant to serve 20 days Huber, consecutive, as penalty for failure to attend Victim Impact Panel.

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.

Count #2:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 MONTHS Jail; (consecutive to Count #1).

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS; (probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County).

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Perform 50 Hours Community Service.
*Not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
